devdoc.details: The Ownable contract has an owner address, and provides basic authorization control functions, this simplifies the implementation of "user permissions". A special address 'master' can transfer ownership.

constructor.details: The Ownable constructor sets the original 'owner' of the contract to the sender account.

renounceOwnership().details: Allows the current owner to relinquish control of the contract.

transferOwnership(address).details: Allows the master to transfer control of the contract to a newOwner.

params._newOwner: The address to transfer ownership to.
